Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteNetFromNetGroup(25.10)                      deleteNetFromNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       deleteNetFromNetGroup - Removes a net from a net group

Syntax
       deleteNetFromNetGroup

       [-help]

       <netGroupName>

       -net {<netName> | <netNameList>}

       Removes  a net from a net group. You can use this command after import-
       ing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deleteNetFromNetGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteNetFromNetGroup

       <netGroupName>
              Specifies  the name of the net group. You can use wildcards (*?)
              with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, required

       -net {<netName> | <netNameList>}
              Specifies the name of the net(s). You  can  use  wildcards  (*?)
              with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command removes net NET1 from net group NG22:

       deleteNetFromNetGroup NG22 NET1

